 Approximately  225{dwellings }of which
 169 are houses, 41 bungalows, 4 shops,
 2  public houses,  6  holiday cottages
 and   3   farmhouses.                 
{Population} was  746  in 1821;  626 in
 1881; 521 in 1981; 518 in October 1985
 &   consists   of:-                   
 Under  1  year  = 5  females, 2 males;
 1 & 2  years    = 7  females, 3 males;
 3 & 4  years    = 8 females, 6 males; 
 5 - 12 years   = 14 females, 17 males;
 13 - 18 years  = 26 females, 20 males;
 19 - 60 years = 156 females, 166 males
 Over 60 years  = 56 females, 32 males;
{                                      
{Total } =  272  females ,  246  males.

 More homes  are  being  built  but the
 population   is  decreasing and aging.
